<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1321,839,945]" box="[264,389,839,864]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[264,389,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1321,839,945]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[312,437,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Attenuatus</emphasis>
(Latin) = drawn out, tapered. This name is used as an adjective and refers to the narrowed, extended gonocoxite, lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[873,960,919,945]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–93" captionStartId="25.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[286,1290,334,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-78@25.[268,1318,296,1736]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 71–93. Brachylinga spp. gonocoxite, lateral view. 71. albifrons. 72. albiseta. 73. attenuata. 74. baccata. 75. bicolor. 76. chilensis. 77. cinerea. 78. clausa. 79. concava. 80. curacaoensis. 81. divaricata. 82. fraterna. 83. laculata. 84. mexicana. 85. mimica. 86. morata. 87. ornatifrons. 88. pavida. 89. punctifrons. 90. sericeifrons. 91. tepocae. 92. tridentata. 93. xanthoperna. Scale = 0.1 mm." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,999,1305]" box="[264,383,999,1024]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[264,383,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,999,1305]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webb" authorityYear="2006" box="[312,575,1039,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Brachylinga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis box="[312,575,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brachylinga attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is taxonomically associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1089,1039,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Brachylinga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clausa">
<emphasis box="[979,1089,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">B. clausa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in possessing setae on the katepisternum; in having the halter knob yellow; and in having the gonocoxite attenuate in ventral (
<figureCitation box="[503,589,1119,1145]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="21.[264,382,1747,1771]" captionTargetBox="[332,1286,317,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[303,1319,310,1753]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Brachylinga spp. sternite 8, gonocoxite ventral view. 25. albifrons. 26. albiseta. 27. attenuata. 28. baccata. 29. bicolor. 30. chilensis. 31. cinerea. 32. clausa. 33. concava. 34. curacaoensis. 35. divaricata. 36. fraterna. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: Gx = gonocoxite, Gs = gonostylus, H = hypandrium, S8 = sternite 8, VL = ventral lobe." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) and lateral views (
<figureCitation box="[817,905,1119,1145]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–93" captionStartId="25.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[286,1290,334,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-78@25.[268,1318,296,1736]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 71–93. Brachylinga spp. gonocoxite, lateral view. 71. albifrons. 72. albiseta. 73. attenuata. 74. baccata. 75. bicolor. 76. chilensis. 77. cinerea. 78. clausa. 79. concava. 80. curacaoensis. 81. divaricata. 82. fraterna. 83. laculata. 84. mexicana. 85. mimica. 86. morata. 87. ornatifrons. 88. pavida. 89. punctifrons. 90. sericeifrons. 91. tepocae. 92. tridentata. 93. xanthoperna. Scale = 0.1 mm." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1206,1119,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Brachylinga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clausa">
<emphasis box="[1097,1206,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">B. clausa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the posterior margin of the hypoproct rounded (
<figureCitation box="[834,907,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–13" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1747,1771]" captionTargetBox="[308,1278,313,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-78@19.[284,1300,310,1728]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 2–13. Brachylinga spp. tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 2. albifrons. 3. albiseta. 4. attenuata. 5. baccata. 6. bicolor. 7. chilensis. 8. cinerea. 9. clausa. 10. concava. 11. curacaoensis. 12. divaricata. 13. fraterna. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, Epa = epandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, SS = sensory seta, T8 = tergite 8." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); the apex of the distiphallus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 117–139" captionStartId="27.[264,382,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[291,1315,327,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-78@27.[272,1316,315,1723]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 117–139. Brachylinga spp. aedeagus, dorsal view. 117. albifrons. 118. albiseta. 119. attenuata. 120. baccata. 121. bicolor. 122. chilensis. 123. cinerea. 124. clausa. 125. concava. 126. curacaoensis. 127. divaricata. 128. fraterna. 129. laculata. 130. mexicana. 131. mimica. 132. morata. 133. ornatifrons. 134. pavida. 135. punctifrons. 136. sericeifrons. 137. tepocae. 138. tridentata. 139. xanthoperna. Scale = 0.1 mm." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 119</figureCitation>
) tapered to a point; the ventral apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[801,901,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–162" captionStartId="28.[264,383,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[294,1292,321,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-76@28.[260,1327,296,1684]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 140–162. Brachylinga spp. aedeagus, ventral view. 140. albifrons. 141. albiseta. 142. attenuata. 143. baccata. 144. bicolor. 145. chilensis. 146. cinerea. 147. clausa. 148. concava. 149. curacaoensis. 150. divaricata. 151. fraterna. 152. laculata. 153. mexicana. 154. mimica. 155. morata. 156. ornatifrons. 157. pavida. 158. punctifrons. 159. sericeifrons. 160. tepocae. 161. tridentata. 162. xanthoperna. Scale = 0.1 mm." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 142</figureCitation>
) of the male aedeagus extending to anterior margin of dorsal apodeme; and the distiphallus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1202,1239,1265]" captionStart="FIGURES 163–185" captionStartId="29.[264,383,1709,1733]" captionTargetBox="[289,1285,327,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-78@29.[269,1318,315,1705]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 163–185. Brachylinga spp. aedeagus, lateral view. 163. albifrons. 164. albiseta. 165. attenuata. 166. baccata. 167. bicolor. 168. chilensis. 169. cinerea. 170. clausa. 171. concava. 172. curacaoensis. 173. divaricata. 174. fraterna. 175. laculata. 176. mexicana. 177. mimica. 178. morata. 179. ornatifrons. 180. pavida. 181. punctifrons. 182. sericeifrons. 183. tepocae. 184. tridentata. 185. xanthoperna. Scale = 0.1 mm." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 165</figureCitation>
) recurved anteroventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,1359,1905]" box="[264,779,1359,1384]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[264,779,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[439,540,1359,1384]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">holotype</typeStatus>
male (MEI 046047)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,1359,1905]" box="[312,560,1399,1425]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Body length 
<quantity box="[463,557,1399,1425]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,1359,1905]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,385,1438,1464]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Head.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[516,641,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.78">0.78 mm</quantity>
. Ommatidia smaller ventrally and laterally. Frons pruinescence gray, brownish gray dorsally; setae dark brown on dorsal half. Antenna/head length 0.60; scape and pedicel dark reddish brown, pruinescence gray, first flagellomere dark yellow, second and third flagellomeres dark brown; scape length 
<quantity box="[1078,1184,1559,1585]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
, length/width 1.2, scape/pedicel length 1.7, scape/flagellum width 0.77, setae yellow, short; pedicel length 
<quantity box="[520,631,1639,1665]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
, length/width 0.7; flagellum length 
<quantity box="[1068,1178,1639,1665]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.28">0.28 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
, length/width 2.2, flagellum/scape width 2.3. Parafacial pruinescence white. Maxillary palpus dark yellow; length 
<quantity box="[743,857,1719,1745]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.30 mm</quantity>
, length/width 5.0; setae pale yellow, elongate. Genal setae white. Occipital setae white becoming lanceolate, appressed dorsally. Postocular macrosetae dark reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,1359,1905]" lastBlockId="34.[264,1325,284,1273]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,411,1838,1864]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Thorax.</emphasis>
Macrosetae dark reddish brown, 3 np, 2 sa, 1 pa, 2 dc, 2 sc. Mesonotum dark brown pruinescence brownish gray; setae dark brown, short intermixed with white, lanceolate, appressed setae. Pleuron and scutellum dark reddish brown, pruinescence white; setae white on propleuron, anepisternum, katepisternum, metanepisternum, laterotergite, and scutellum. 
<emphasis box="[628,696,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Wing.</emphasis>
Membrane pale gray, veins brown, pale yellow anteriorly; length 
<quantity box="[485,583,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
, length/width 3.2; pterostigma dark yellow; cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1219,1227,420,434]" fontSize="6" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">3</subScript>
closed, petiolate. Halter pale yellow. 
<emphasis box="[633,696,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Legs.</emphasis>
Coxa setae white, present on posterior surface of midcoxa; macrosetae dark reddish brown. Fore­ and midfemora reddish brown, midfemur dark yellow apically, hindfemur dark yellowish brown, apex brown; ventral setae white on fore­ and midfemora; av 0:0:4, pv 0:0:2. Tibiae dark yellow, apex dark reddish brown. Tarsomeres 1–2 dark yellow, apex dark reddish brown; 3–5 pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1325,284,1273]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,441,647,673]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Pale reddish brown, pruinescence white; dorsal setae white, appressed; lateral setae white. 
<taxonomicName box="[496,623,687,712]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[496,623,687,712]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Terminalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Reddish brown. Tergite 8 (
